    <note type="biography">
        <p>Botanist, entomologist, and social reformer. President, Botanical Society of Edinburgh, 1839, 1846, and 1866; honorary secretary, from <hi rend="italic">circa</hi> 1861 until 1866. Edited the <hi rend="italic">Amethyst, or Christian’s Annual</hi>, 1832–4; secretary of the Sabbath Alliance; one of the compilers of the <hi rend="italic">Church of England hymn-book</hi> (1838). Vice-president of the Anti-slavery Convention, 1840. Earned a living as a landscape painter in his later years.</p></note>
